Ugly numbers are positive numbers whose prime factors only include 2, 3, 5. For example, 6, 8 are ugly while 14 is not ugly since it includes another prime factor 7.
Note that 1 is typically treated as an ugly number. The sequence 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 8, 9, 10, 12, 15, ‚Ä¶ shows the first 11 ugly numbers. By convention, 1 is considered to be ugly number.
