A> With each iteration, I am taking the the upper half‚Äôs value (calculated by deducting the current position by the string length), which is then temporary stored in a temp variable.
B> Then swap that value with the lower half‚Äôs value. So, for the fist iteration, I will replace, the last element with the first element of the array.
C> In the next iteration, I will swap the second last upper half element, with second last lower-half element.
D> So, we only need to traverse half of the array, to swap all the lower and upper half element.
