Let‚Äôs take a look at how we updated state in our class-based component:

`onChange={ (event) => this.setState({ email: event.target.value })`

With hooks, we no longer need this or this.setState() since we‚Äôre already initiating our state variables and attaching a setter. Since we only have two variables we‚Äôre using, we‚Äôre going to use an inline function to call the setter that we initiated in useState for each input. We‚Äôll also add our value back without the this prefix.

