## Object serialization

Object serialization is the process of converting an object‚Äôs state to a string from which it can later be restored. ECMAScript 5 provides native functions JSON.stringify() and JSON.parse() to serialize and restore JavaScript objects. These functions use the JSON data interchange format.

By convention, the top-level state in React, is an object or some other key-value collection like a Map, but technically it can be any type. Still, you should do your best to keep the state serializable. Don't put anything inside it that you can't easily turn into JSON.

